{"lemma": "خِلْفَةٌ", "slug": "خِلْفَةٌ", "root": "خ.ل.ف", "root_slug": "خ-ل-ف", "root_link": "/words/roots/خ-ل-ف", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "خِلْفَة", "root": "خلف", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n11356"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "succession", "fa": "جانشینی", "ur": "جانشینی", "tr": "devamlılık", "id": "suksesi", "bn": "পরবর্তীতা", "es": "sucesión", "fr": "succession", "de": "Nachfolge", "ru": "преемственность", "zh": "继任"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n11356", "headword_ar": "خِلْفَةٌ", "root": "xlf", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "a subst. signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A mode,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "manner, of coming after"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "behind"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qiEodapN", "text_ar": "قِعْدَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying “ a mode, or manner, of sitting. ” (Msb.) ―         -b2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xulofN", "text_ar": "خُلْفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b3-  It signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Difference"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of any kind"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (K, * TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "coming and going"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the night and the day; (S, K, * TA;) and likewise of wild animals. (K.) Hence the saying in the Kur [xxv. 63],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wahuwa A@l~a*iY jaEala A@ll~ayola waA@ln~ahaAra", "text_ar": "وَهُوَ ا@لَّذِى جَعَلَ ا@للَّيْلَ وَا@لنَّهَارَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofapF", "text_ar": "خِلْفَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K, *) meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*awaY xilofapK", "text_ar": "ذَوَى خِلْفَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Bd,) i. e. ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And He it is who hath made the night and the day"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so that each replaces the other:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "each follows the other:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, * TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so that he who is unable to accomplish a thing in the night may do it in the day, and the reverse."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr, L, K.) Zuheyr says, of wild animals,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yamo$iyna xilofapF", "text_ar": "يَمْشِينَ خِلْفَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They go to and fro."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA. [See Em p. 109.]) And one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axa*atohu xilofapN", "text_ar": "اَخَذَتْهُ خِلْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He was"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 797}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "taken with"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an affection causing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a frequent going to and from the privy."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K.) [And hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofapN", "text_ar": "خِلْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A discharging of the bowels;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a purging and vomiting together;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a disordered state of the stomach arising from"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "unwholesome"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "food;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a looseness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "diarrhœa."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK, TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofN", "text_ar": "خِلْفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b5-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bringing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of camels"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the watering-place in the evening, after the people have gone away."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K.) ―         -b6-  And A man's"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "watching to see another,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ano yunaAZira", "text_ar": "اَنْ يُنَاظِرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in some copies of the K, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "An yunaASira", "text_ar": "ان يُنَاصِرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in other copies, being put for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "An yubaASiru", "text_ar": "ان يُبَاصِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is the right reading, agreeably with an explanation of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aixotalafa", "text_ar": "اِخْتَلَفَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaAHibahu", "text_ar": "صَاحِبَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [for which see 3, near the middle of the paragraph,] TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and when he is absent from his family, going in to them,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,) or [rather],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when he is absent from his wife, going in to her."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA, after the explanation of the phrase above mentioned.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A thing that is suspended behind the rider;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as is suspended behind the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kind of vehicle called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maHomil", "text_ar": "مَحْمِل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Remains"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of water in a trough or tank. (TA.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What remains, of food, between the teeth."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lh, K.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A plant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "herbage, that comes forth after another plant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "other herbage,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which has become dry, and broken in pieces:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that comes forth not from rain, but by reason of the cold of the latter part of the night."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Aboo-Ziyád El-Kilábee, K. [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rabolN", "text_ar": "رَبْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What the trees disclose in the beginning of the cold,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by reason of the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rain called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Safariy~ap", "text_ar": "صَفَرِيَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fruit that comes forth after other fruit:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fruit that comes forth after abundant fruit;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, TA;) this being termed the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofap", "text_ar": "خِلْفَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of trees: (S, Mgh:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a growth of leaves after the falling away of other leaves:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, * TA:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duwna", "text_ar": "دُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the K is a mistake for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baEoda", "text_ar": "بَعْدَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "leaves that come forth after the first leaves, in the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "season called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Sayof", "text_ar": "صَيْف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Nh, TA.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What grows in the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Sayof", "text_ar": "صَيْف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "summer"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; so says A 'Obeyd: (S, K:) or, (JK, Mgh, K,) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofN", "text_ar": "خِلْفٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "herbage produced by the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Syf", "text_ar": "صيف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (JK, K,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Syf", "text_ar": "صيف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mgh,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "after the springherbage has dried up."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK, Mgh.) ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A produce of grape-vines after the grapes have turned black; the grapes being gathered while it is fresh and green, it then ripens:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so other fruits:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a new produce, by the vine, of fresh sour grapes."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b8-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Grain that is sown"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK, * Mgh, K *)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "after the former has come to maturity:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, TA:) because taken as a substitute for wheat and barley: (K:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilafN", "text_ar": "خِلَفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Mgh.) ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A piece with which a garment is patched"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when it is old and worn out."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b10-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A time after a time."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, K.)       -A3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Differing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one from another"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "others"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofN", "text_ar": "خِلْفٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) it is applied in this sense to a people, or company of men: (AZ, S, K:) and to beasts, or horses or the like, as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "differing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in their colours and appearances:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofataAni", "text_ar": "خِلْفَتَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied to any two things that are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "different;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ks, TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofaAni", "text_ar": "خِلْفَانِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Ks, Msb, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofapN", "text_ar": "خِلْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofataAni", "text_ar": "خِلْفَتَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Ks, TA,) to any two colours that are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "combined"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[because"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "different"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Ks, K, TA.) AZ cites, as an ex., the saying [of a rájiz],"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "saAqiyaAhumaA ↓ \n      dalowaAYo xilofaAni"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "My two buckets are different, and their two suppliers with water"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S, TA;) meaning that one of them [i. e. of the buckets] is ascending and full, and the other is descending and empty; or that one of them is new, and the other is old and worn out. (TA, in two places.) And one says of two children, or two male slaves; or two female slaves, that they are"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofataAni", "text_ar": "خِلْفَتَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Ks, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofaAni", "text_ar": "خِلْفَانِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) applying to the male and the female, (TA,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One tall and the other short:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one white and the other black."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ks, K.) One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banuw fulaAnK", "text_ar": "بَنُو فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofapN", "text_ar": "خِلْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The children of such a one are half males and half females."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nitaAju fulaAnK", "text_ar": "نِتَاجُ فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofapN", "text_ar": "خِلْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The offspring of the beasts of such a one are one year male and another year female."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK, TA.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waladato xilofayoni", "text_ar": "وَلَدَتْ خِلْفَيْنِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", said of ewe or goat, (K,) or of a camel, (L,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She brought forth one year a male and another year a female."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K.) The pl. [of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofN", "text_ar": "خِلْفٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (K, TA) in all its senses (TA) is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axolaAfN", "text_ar": "اَخْلَافٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilafapN", "text_ar": "خِلَفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (K, * TA;) the latter, [in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilofapN", "text_ar": "خِلْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qiradapN", "text_ar": "قِرَدَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qirodN", "text_ar": "قِرْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["Bd", "K", "TA", "S", "Msb", "Mgh", "JK", "AZ", "Ks", "L"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}